HEADWORD: Suspensation
<hw>Sus`pen*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>suspensatio</ets> suspension from a charge or benefice.]</ety>
<def>The act of suspending, or the state of being suspended, especially
for a short time; temporary suspension.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

